Appendix D: Survey Instruments (Abridged)

D.1 Trust (Mayer & Davis, 1999) – 8 items, 7‑point Likert

1. The facilitator/process was capable of performing its role effectively.
2. The facilitator/process was competent.
3. The facilitator/process was trustworthy.
4. The facilitator/process kept my best interests in mind.
5. The facilitator/process was honest.
6. The facilitator/process was reliable.
7. I felt confident in the facilitator/process.
8. The facilitator/process acted with integrity.

D.2 Procedural Fairness (Colquitt, 2001) – 7 items, 7‑point Likert

1. I was able to express my views and feelings during the meeting.
2. I had influence over the outcome.
3. The process was applied consistently.
4. The process was free of bias.
5. The process was based on accurate information.
6. I was treated with dignity and respect.
7. I was treated with courtesy.

D.3 Cognitive Load (Paas, 1992) – single item

On a scale of 1–9, how much mental effort did this meeting require? (1 = very, very low, 9 = very, very high)

